S E N A T E R E S O L U T I O N
EXPRESSING DEEPEST CONDOLENCES ON THE PASSING OF HILDING T. MUNSON
Introduced By: Senators Sosnowski, Felag, LaMountain, Acosta, Bell, Zurier, Quezada,
Gu, Lauria, and Paolino
Date Introduced: February 11, 2025
Referred To: Recommended for Immediate Consideration
1 WHEREAS, It is with deep sadness that this Senate has learned of the passing of Hilding
2 T. Munson, the beloved husband of Judith A. Munson for 48 years. He was the son of the late
3 Hilding K. and Alice R. Munson; and
4 WHEREAS, Hilding Munson was a graduate of Bishop Hendricken High School, and the
5 University of Rhode Island. Mr. Munson was a hard-working youngster who delivered the
6 Providence Journal and worked summers in construction. Mr. Munson also served our nation
7 with honor and distinction as a member of the United States Army and served in Korea during the
8 Vietnam War era; and
9 WHEREAS, Mr. Munson worked hard his entire life and strove daily to provide for his
10 family and loved ones. He was a life-long paper carrier, delivered flowers for Scott the Florist,
11 served as a Rhode Island State Correctional Officer, and for thirty-five years he served our State
12 with distinction as a Rhode Island State Sheriff, retiring with the rank of Sergeant; and
13 WHEREAS, Mr. Munson’s proudest accomplishment as a professional was his 63-year
14 tenure of devoted service with the Snug Harbor Volunteer Fire Department. He was a Captain for
15 twenty years and was currently serving as the President of the Snug Harbor Fire Department. He
16 was also known locally as the South Kingstown Police Department Traffic Constable and
17 thoroughly enjoyed working details; and
18 WHEREAS, Hilding Munson was passionate about serving his local community. He was
19 a dedicated and longtime volunteer with the Special Olympics, RI, for whom he worked every
20 summer for over fifty years. Mr. Munson was a proud member of the VFW 916 and took great

1 pride in decorating veterans’ graves on Memorial Day. He was also a man of faith and was an
2 active member of Christ the King Church in Kingston; and
3 WHEREAS, In addition to his wife, Judith, Mr. Munson leaves behind his children
4 Kristin M. Munson and her husband, Brandon Morgan, and Hilding T. Munson, II and his wife,
5 Alba Davenport. Mr. Munson also leaves behind his sisters, Lynn Mary Munson and Teresa C.
6 Giviens, and a nephew Ryan D. Giviens. He was predeceased by his sister, Patrice A. Munson;
7 now, therefore be it
8 RESOLVED, That this Senate of the State of Rhode Island hereby expresses its deepest
9 condolences to the Munson Family on the passing of Hilding T. Munson; and be it further
10 RESOLVED, That the Secretary of State be and hereby is authorized and directed to
11 transmit a duly certified copy of this resolution to Judith A. Munson and Family.
